    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="134"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/462.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador to Great Britain</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You may assure the Minister for Foreign Affairs that this Government has no
                    objection whatever to Japan and Russia having copies of the loan agreement and
                    accompanying statements explaining currency program and specifying Manchurian
                    enterprises.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
